{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | name=Kurihara Shrine | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] |image=[[File:Kurihara shrine.jpg|300px]] | location=[[Gifu Prefecture]] [[Takayama City]], Kamitakara Town, Miyahara 350 | coordinates={{Coord|36|17|9.60|N|137|22|19.51|E|scale:30000}} | deity=[[Itakeru no Mikoto]], and others | type={{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}}, {{ill|Gōsha|ja|郷社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gōsha|qq=}} | consecration_year=Unknown | Main Festival=May 3 }}
'''Kurihara Shrine''' (栗原神社) is a [[Shinto shrine]] located in [[Takayama City]], [[Gifu Prefecture]], within the Kamitakara area (formerly [[Yoshiki District]], [[Kamitakara Village]]). It is situated near the Kamitakara Branch Office of Takayama City (formerly the Kamitakara Village Office).
The shrine is identified as one of the {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} listed in the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|2=ja|3=延喜式神名帳|4=zh|5=延喜式神名帳|6=simple|7=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} for [[Hida Province]], being one of eight such shrines in the region.
During the [[Edo period]], the shrine was known as {{ill|Hakusan Gongen|ja|白山権現|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hakusan Gongen|qq=}}. In the 3rd year of the [[Meiji era]] (1870), it was officially recognized as the Shikinaisha Kurihara Shrine and renamed accordingly.
